Might improve mileage at highway speeds. but the weight of the panels would
decrease stop-an-go mileage...The figure I've seen bandied about most is 15
HP to "keep" one ton moving at 60 mph on the flat...It's the getting there 
that
uses up the most fuel (remember the ill-fated 4-6-8 cylinder Caddy?).

